MV 2: mv_biomass_composition

Purpose: Full analysis data per resource per parameter. Covers all 8 analysis types shown on the Characterization tab: compositional, proximate, ultimate, XRF, ICP, calorimetry, XRD, and FT-NIR. Also used for Overview tab charts and dynamic range filtering.
Grain: One row per resource × county × parameter × analysis type (aggregated across experiments within that county)
Aggregation approach: Because the grain includes geoid, this view does not contain a pre-aggregated "all counties" row. When the Characterization tab is shown without a county filter, Cube.js aggregates across all county rows at query time — using SUM(avg_value * observation_count) / SUM(observation_count) for weighted average, and MIN(min_value) / MAX(max_value) for ranges. std_dev is only displayed in the UI when a specific county is selected — it cannot be correctly reconstructed from county-level pre-aggregates, and is scientifically ambiguous when mixing samples from different counties.
