Additional Tables

These are plain transactional tables (not materialized views) managed by the web engineering team. They are not part of the ETL pipeline and do not need a refresh schedule.
biomass_resource_images

Purpose: Stores one or more image URLs per resource to support image carousels on the profile page. Decoupled from mv_biomass_search so new images can be added by simply inserting new rows with GCS bucket URLs — no schema changes required.
Grain: One row per resource per image
Why a plain table (not an MV): Images don't require aggregation or ETL joins. A plain table is simpler to update (insert new rows pointing to GCS bucket URLs) and is managed independently by the web engineering team.
API exposure: The profile API returns images as an ordered array. The frontend iterates and renders the carousel. Starting with one image and adding more is fully backward-compatible.
Default image: The row with the lowest sort_order (typically 0) is used as the default/primary image — equivalent to what mv_biomass_search.image_url currently holds. Once this table is fully populated, image_url in the search MV can be dropped.
