Refresh Strategy

These views are relatively small (< 10,000 rows total). Recommended approach:
Use REFRESH MATERIALIZED VIEW CONCURRENTLY (allows reads during refresh, requires a UNIQUE index on each view)
Refresh all 9 views after each ETL run, or on a daily cron as a fallback
Frequency
When
After each ETL run
Whenever new data is loaded into the source tables
Daily (fallback)
If no ETL trigger exists, a nightly cron is sufficient
On-demand
We can also call a refresh manually during development
PostgreSQL Extensions

Confirmed present on the database:
pg_trgm — trigram similarity for fuzzy/typo-tolerant search
unaccent — accent-insensitive search
btree_gin — combined B-tree + GIN indexes
No additional extensions needed.
Schema Placement

We recommend placing these views in a dedicated schema (e.g., biocirv_app), but public or ca_biositing also works. We just need to know the schema so we can configure our Django models to point to the correct db_table.
Summary: What We Need

Create the 9 materialized views with the columns defined above (column names can differ — just let us know the final schema)
Add the recommended indexes for each view (critical for search and filter performance)
Pick a schema and tell us the name
Set up a refresh trigger or cron (daily or after ETL)
We are happy to iterate on column definitions if your internal schema differs or if adjustments are needed. The column names and types are what matter most for our Django model mapping.
